[{"id":"VR708793","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three circles with the same center. The radii of the three circles are 0.5 meters, 1.0 meter, and 1.5 meters, respectively. On the innermost circle, an upward force of 2 newtons is exerted directly to the right of the center of the circle. On the middle circle, a rightward force of 2 newtons is exerted directly above the center. On the outermost circle, a rightward force of 2 newtons is exerted directly below the center.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR708793.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three disks are attached together and can rotate together about an axis through their common center, as shown in the figure. The disks have radii of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.5\"><math alttext=\"0.5\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.5</mn></math></span></span> meter, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.0\"><math alttext=\"1.0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.0</mn></math></span></span> meter, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.5\"><math alttext=\"1.5\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.5</mn></math></span></span> meters, and each disk has a force of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> newtons exerted at the locations and in the directions shown. What is the magnitude of the net torque about the center of the three-disk system?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR708793_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 newton meters\"><math alttext=\"0 newton meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>N</mtext><mo>路</m